{
  "stem": "443.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was-- because we arrived-- the last day, we arrived at night.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We arrived to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] [BACKGROUND NOISE] When we arrived in Auschwitz, we see the whole camp was lit up, just like this light here, from every side.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was big lights.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And dogs barking, and soldiers, the SS were-- surrounded.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "All of us, as we arrived in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But on the way coming to Auschwitz, we didn't have any food, only what we took along with us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The last couple days, already, we were eating dry wheat, barley.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We were chewing on barley.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "We were eating dry beans because we were so hungry.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "There was no-- nothing to eat.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They didn't give us anything for all the duration, from the time that they took us away from-- from our city.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Some people couldn't make it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Some people died.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We had a lot of people dead when we arrived to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And [SIGHS] the stink on the train, was-- you cannot describe it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "It's unbelievable how people-- we were packed like herrings, so you can imagine what it felt like.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We couldn't sleep.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was no way to sleep, so we slept standing up, leaning one on another.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "When we arrived, already, the train was like half empty because some of them couldn't make it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When we arrived to Auschwitz, I remember they were-- [SIGHS] they were hollering in German, but we understood because we spoke Jewish in the house.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So we understood a little bit what they were talking about.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Then they took the younger ones on one side, and the older ones on another side, mothers and kids on another side.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And we stayed the whole night to be-- to wait, to tell us what to do.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
